description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic, motivated and organised individual to join the Medical Human Resource Team and Diversity and Inclusion Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need an effective and efficient communicator to work in this varied role. You will be required to undertake and prioritise a variety of administrative and clerical duties supporting the Staff Network meetings, minute taking, facilitating agendas, collating action points, sending reports, arranging meetings, you will also provide a varied administrative function to the Medical Human Resource team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a new role and therefore will develop over time to meet the needs of both teams providing administrative support to the Medical HR Team and Diversity and Inclusion Team we envisage the successful candidate will have input into shaping this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full time role working Monday to Friday. The role will be working 3 days with the Medical Human Resources Team and 2 Days with the Diversity and Inclusion Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we are looking for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate ideally will have strong interpersonal skills, ability to prioritise tasks, effective time management with the ability to work calmly under pressure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are able to demonstrate the essential skills required, have a flexible approach to your duties, have sufficient confidence and skills to work independently when needed, can prioritise and work to tight deadlines and have the ability to work on your own initiative as part of two, supportive teams we look forward to hearings from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It would be an advantage if you have had experience of working in a Medical HR environment or have had previous experience of supporting Staff Network meeting or Equivalent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameJacque DixonJob titleMedical Staffing ManagerEmail addressJacqueline.Dixon3@nhs.netTelephone number01622 724157 or 07824509668Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
